text: Rolf Koschorrek (17 June 1956 â€“ 12 January 2020) was a German politician. He was a member of the Christian Democratic Union (CDU). He was a member of the national Bundestag from 2005 to 2013. He was in the dentistry industry outside of politics. Koschorrek was born in Bad Bramstedt. On 12 January 2020, he died of cancer in Berlin.
